name: Mumbai Indians v Chennai Super Kings

name: Chennai Super Kings v Mumbai Indians

name: Punjab Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: Kings XI Punjab apply late strangle on Sunrisers Hyderabad to seal incredible win.

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Chennai Super Kings

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Delhi Capitals

name: Delhi Capitals v Royal Challengers Bangalore

name: Punjab Kings v Mumbai Indians
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium

name: Delhi Capitals v Kolkata Knight Riders

name: Punjab Kings v Delhi Capitals
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Alzarri Joseph's record-breaking 6 for 12 routs Sunrisers Hyderabad. Kieron Pollard's 46 not out off 26 balls lifted Mumbai Indians to a respectable total before Joseph produced one of the great IPL bowling performances

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Delhi Capitals
highlights: Iyer's 67 consigns Royal Challengers Bangalore to sixth straight defeat. This is the joint-worst streak of losses in IPL history; Capitals meanwhile record their third win in six games

name: Rajasthan Royals v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Chris Lynn and Sunil Narine blow away sluggish Rajasthan Royals. Royals made the worst ever IPL total for the loss of three or fewer wickets, and when KKR's openers walloped 65 in the Powerplay, the result was a foregone conclusion

name: Punjab Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: KL Rahul the hero as Kings XI Punjab remain unbeaten at home. Agarwal plays his part with a half-century before chase got tense; Warner's unbeaten 70 in vain

name: Chennai Super Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Chahar, spinners maintain CSK's perfect home record. Chennai Super Kings stomped all over Kolkata Knight Riders to register a seven-wicket victory and claim pole position halfway through the IPL season

name: Mumbai Indians v Punjab Kings
highlights: Kieron Pollard's 83 off 31 seals unlikely Mumbai Indians win. The innings eclipsed KL Rahul's century for Kings XI Punjab, and single-handedly dragged the hosts to victory when they needed 133 off their last 10 overs

name: Rajasthan Royals v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Santner's last-ball six seals dramatic win after Dhoni, Rayudu fifties. Super Kings made the required 18 off a controversial last over - during which a no-ball was revoked - after falling to 24 for 4 in the Powerplay

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Delhi Capitals
highlights: High-flying Shikhar Dhawan fires Delhi Capitals into the top four. He stayed unbeaten on 97 to see Capitals cruised home in a potentially tricky chase; Pant chipped in with 46

name: Mumbai Indians v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Buttler fifty sets up sloppy Royals win. The result ended Mumbai's three-match winning streak while Royals notched just their second win of the season

name: Punjab Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Kohli, de Villiers mastery trumps Gayle's 99*. RCB overcome sequence of six successive loss in style; Kings XI consigned to first loss at home this season

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Raina and Jadeja script another last-over CSK win. Chennai Super Kings extended their winning streak to four matches and lengthened their lead at the top of the table in IPL 2019

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Delhi Capitals
highlights: Sunrisers Hyderabad lose 8 for 15 and their third successive game. Kagiso Rabada and Keemo Paul played starring roles for Delhi Capitals, claiming seven wickets and six catches between them

name: Mumbai Indians v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Lasith Malinga and Hardik Pandya hand RCB their seventh defeat. AB de Villiers and Moeen Ali hit fifties, but a series of significant contributions from Mumbai Indians' batsmen helped the hosts chase down 172 at the Wankhede

name: Punjab Kings v Rajasthan Royals
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: R Ashwin delivers the thrill as Kings XI return to winning ways. He first hit a four-ball 17 not out and then returned to dismiss the set Sanju Samson and Rahul Tripathi to choke Royals

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Rashid Khan, David Warner snap Sunrisers Hyderabad's losing streak. They toppled a Dhoni-less Chennai Super Kings side to secure a vital victory after three losses on the trot

name: Delhi Capitals v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Pandya brothers, Chahar star in Mumbai's emphatic win. Chasing 169, Capitals laboured to 128 for 9 and suffered their third loss in four games at home this season

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Kohli hundred gives RCB victory despite Rana, Russell scare. Andre Russell and Nitish Rana plundered a barrage of boundaries in the death overs but fell short in the last over

name: Rajasthan Royals v Mumbai Indians
highlights: New captain Smith leads Royals home to keep their campaign alive. The five-wicket win was set up by some excellent bowling from Shreyas Gopal and Jofra Archer

name: Delhi Capitals v Punjab Kings
highlights: Shikhar Dhawan, Shreyas Iyer fifties guide Delhi Capitals to rare home win. Fifties from Shreyas Iyer and Shikhar Dhawan ensured Delhi Capitals survived a late wobble to beat Kings XI Punjab

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Warner and Bairstow punish sloppy Knight Riders. The Sunrisers Hyderabad batting pair put on 131 in just 12.2 overs, which reduced the 160-run chase to a cakewalk in the end

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Royal Challengers Bangalore win last-ball thriller; Dhoni's 84* in vain. With 26 to get in the last over, the Super Kings captain got it down to two off one ball before being beaten by Umesh's gutsy change of pace

name: Rajasthan Royals v Delhi Capitals
highlights: Pant's brilliance puts Rahane century in the shade. The win means Capitals moved to the top of the IPL 2019 points table, the first time the franchise from Delhi has attained that position in the second half of an IPL season since 2012.

name: Chennai Super Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: Shane Watson's 96 helps CSK maintain their spotless home record. After going ten innings without a half-century, the opener roared back to form with an innings reminiscent of his century in last season's final

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Punjab Kings
highlights: AB de Villiers' 82* keeps RCB's playoff hopes alive. A target of 203 proved beyond Kings XI's reach despite aggressive knocks from KL Rahul and Nicholas Pooran

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Dinesh Karthik's 97* in vain after Riyan Parag and Jofra Archer's late fireworks. Chasing 176, Rajasthan Royals slipped to 123 for six before their seventh-wicket pair turned the tide with a partnership of 44 in 21 balls

name: Chennai Super Kings v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Irresistible Mumbai complete the double against Super Kings. Krunal, Bumrah and Malinga induce a collapse after Rohit's first fifty of IPL 2019 leads Mumbai to an above-par total on a tired Chepauk surface

name: Rajasthan Royals v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: Livingstone, Samson, Unadkat keep Royals' playoff hopes alive. Samson completes the chase without breaking a sweat after a lightning start from the openers and a fine bowling performance in the death

name: Delhi Capitals v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Delhi Capitals hold off Royal Challengers Bangalore to make playoffs after six-year gap. Amit Mishra and Kagiso Rabada lead a strong performance with the ball after fifties from Shikhar Dhawan and Shreyas Iyer

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Russell's 80* off 40 trumps Hardik's 91 off 34 as Knight Riders stay alive. Kolkata Knight Riders keep their IPL alive thanks to an all-round performance from their biggest match-winner

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Punjab Kings
highlights: David Warner's 81 and Rashid Khan's three-for blow Kings XI Punjab away. The Australian opener ended his IPL stint with a ninth fifty-plus score, which set up a 200-plus score and solidified Sunrisers Hyderabad's playoff hopes

name: Chennai Super Kings v Delhi Capitals
highlights: Dhoni, Jadeja and Tahir send Capitals on a tailspin. Raina's half-century turned around CSK's floundering innings before Dhoni delivered the blockbuster finish

name: Mumbai Indians v Sunrisers Hyderabad
result: Match tied (Mumbai Indians won the one-over eliminator)
highlights: Mumbai survive Pandey-Nabi scare to seal playoff qualification. Manish Pandey's last-ball six took Sunrisers to the Super Over, but Mumbai cruised to a win after keeping them to 8 in the tie-breaker

name: Punjab Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Shubman Gill leads KKR to stay alive, Kings XI knocked out. Sam Curran's unbeaten 55 off 24 had given Kings XI a competitive total but KKR's top order make short work of it

name: Delhi Capitals v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Capitals finish league stage with win; Royals eliminated. Ishant and Mishra took three wickets each and Pant cracked an unbeaten 53 as Royals paid for a meek batting performance

name: Punjab Kings v Chennai Super Kings
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Chennai Super Kings seal top-two finish despite convincing defeat. Kings XI Punjab ride on KL Rahul's blistering half-century and Nicholas Pooran's finishing job to sign off with six-wicket win

name: Mumbai Indians v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Pandya brothers knock out Knight Riders, Sunrisers qualify. Skillful bowling from them and sensible batting from Rohit took Mumbai Indians to No.1 on the points table

name: Mumbai Indians v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Bravo unleashes stunning assault to bring CSK screaming back. The allrounder hit seven sixes in a 30-ball 68 to snatch victory from what had been a dominant Mumbai Indians side for most of the match

name: Punjab Kings v Delhi Daredevils
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Rahul floors Daredevils with fastest IPL fifty. The opener's 14-ball half-century led Kings XI Punjab to a six-wicket win in Mohali

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Sunil Narine ambushes Royal Challengers again. The Trinidadian smashed a 17-ball half-century to kickstart Knight Riders' chase after Nitish Rana's part-time offspin took out AB de Villiers and Virat Kohli to help restrict RCB to 176

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Sunrisers bowlers prove too much for Royals. Shakib Al Hasan and Rashid Khan picked collective figures of 3 for 46 restrict Rajasthan Royals t0 125 before Shikhar Dhawan slammed a 33-ball half-century to make mockery of a small chase

name: Chennai Super Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: CSK chase 203 in blockbuster finish to homecoming. Sam Billings turned the match around with 56 off 23, leaving Andre Russell on the losing side despite his record 88

name: Rajasthan Royals v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Royals return home with rain-hit victory. Delhi Daredevils were set a target of 71 in six overs, after a rain delay of more than two and a half hours. They never really got going in the chase

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Frazzled Sunrisers squeeze home in last-ball thriller. Sunrisers Hyderabad lost 9 for 75, before the last-wicket pair of Hooda and Stanlake held their nerve to keep Mumbai Indians winless

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Punjab Kings
highlights: Umesh, de Villiers carry RCB past Kings XI. Hosts arrest five-match losing streak at Chinnaswamy courtesy Umesh's three-for and de Villiers' half-century

name: Mumbai Indians v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Roy clinches thrilling win on Daredevils debut. Having looked set for 200-plus, Mumbai Indians stumbled badly in the slog overs, and ended up suffering their third successive defeat

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Sunrisers Hyderabad
result: Sunrisers won by 5 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Ex-Knight Rider Shakib leads Sunrisers to first win in Kolkata. Kolkata Knight Riders were only in control as long as their spinners were bowling, as Sunrisers dominated the rest of the game to consolidate their position at the top of the table

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Sanju Samson outguns RCB's batting might. The batsman hit 10 sixes and launched Rajasthan Royals to 217 for 4, a score that proved too much for Royal Challengers Bangalore

name: Punjab Kings v Chennai Super Kings
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Dhoni falls short in final over, Kings XI prevent a heist. After pulling off two tremendous chases in their first two games, CSK almost did it again in Mohali

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Rana and Russell hand Daredevils a drubbing. Nitish Rana's 59 and a 12-ball 41 from Andre Russell powered Knight Riders to what proved an eminently match-winning total of 200

name: Mumbai Indians v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Rohit, Lewis batter Royal Challengers in imposing win. Mumbai Indians managed to break their three-match losing streak with a massive 46-run win

name: Rajasthan Royals v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 7 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Kuldeep, Chawla, Rana lift KKR to top of table. Spin limited Rajasthan Royals to 160 and an aggressive batting approach then helped Kolkata Knight Riders chase down their target with six balls remaining

name: Punjab Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Gayle's blazing ton hands Sunrisers first loss. The opener smashed his sixth IPL hundred and 21st overall in T20s to lead Kings XI Punjab to 193 for 3, a score that proved too much for Sunrisers Hyderabad

name: Chennai Super Kings v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Royals fall flat after Watson century. The Australia allrounder sizzled against his former team to score his fourth T20 century as Super Kings reigned supreme at their adopted home ground

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Punjab Kings
result: Kings XI won by 9 wickets (with 11 balls remaining) (D/L method)
highlights: Gayle, Rahul launch Kings XI to the top. The two openers smashed fifties in a revised chase of 125 off 13 overs to crush Kolkata Knight Riders

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Delhi Daredevils
result: RCB won by 6 wickets (with 12 balls remaining)
highlights: De Villiers magic powers RCB to thumping win. The South Africa batsman's 39-ball 90, his highest IPL score in a chase, lifted RCB to their second win

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Rayudu, Chahar the difference as CSK pull off another close win. Chennai Super Kings came back from a slow start to post 128 off their last ten overs and edge Sunrisers out in a four-run win

name: Rajasthan Royals v Mumbai Indians
result: Royals won by 3 wickets (with 2 balls remaining)
highlights: Archer, Gowtham hand Mumbai another final-over defeat. Rajasthan Royals' two big uncapped signings turned it on at critical moments to swing an exceedingly tight game

name: Delhi Daredevils v Punjab Kings
highlights: Mujeeb denies Iyer in dramatic last-ball win for Kings XI Punjab. The 17-year-old mystery spinner defended 16 in the last over to put Kings XI Punjab on top of the points table

name: Mumbai Indians v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: Rashid and Kaul sink Mumbai in chase of 119. Despite losing two key bowlers to injury, Sunrisers Hyderabad managed to pull off the second-lowest successful defence in the IPL

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Chennai Super Kings
result: Super Kings won by 5 wickets (with 2 balls remaining)
highlights: Dhoni, Rayudu raze down 206 in blaze of sixes. A stunning 102 runs came off sixes as Chennai Super Kings consigned Royal Challengers Bangalore to another deflating loss at home

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Punjab Kings
highlights: Shakib, Rashid star as Sunrisers defend another low total. Two nights after defending 118, Sunrisers Hyderabad defended 132 to snap Kings XI Punjab's four-match winning streak

name: Delhi Daredevils v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: New captain Iyer's 93* off 40 blows KKR away. A breathtaking innings, a catch, and a run-out. It was a good first day in the office for the new Daredevils captain

name: Chennai Super Kings v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 8 wickets (with 2 balls remaining)
highlights: Rohit stops Mumbai's freefall with match-winning fifty. Mumbai Indians' captain pushed himself up to No. 3 and guided his team to an eight-wicket win against Chennai Super Kings

name: Rajasthan Royals v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: Sunrisers Hyderabad ace another tight defence after batting slump. Their batting slumped after Kane Williamson's half-century, but 151 was plenty for the best attack in the IPL

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 6 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
highlights: KKR batting might too much for de Villiers-less RCB. Virat Kohli steered his side to 175 in Bengaluru, but the KKR top order fired collectively to win with five balls to spare

name: Chennai Super Kings v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Watson, Dhoni muscle CSK to the top. Super Kings blast their third 200-plus score and then see their young fast bowlers Ngidi and Asif impress in their sixth win of the tournament

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Mumbai almost out as RCB finally defend a total. The defending champions failed in a chase of 168 and now need to win all their remaining six matches to stay in playoff contention

name: Delhi Daredevils v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Belligerent top order gives Daredevils enough to edge out Royals. In their second rain-curtailed game against Rajasthan Royals, Delhi Daredevils survived a brutal Jos Buttler attack to lift themselves off the bottom of the table

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Chennai Super Kings
result: KKR won by 6 wickets (with 14 balls remaining)
highlights: Gill and Karthik power KKR past sloppy CSK. The hosts got home with plenty of time to spare after Super Kings' fielding let them down in their attempt to defend 177

name: Punjab Kings v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 6 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Rohit, Krunal blitz keeps Mumbai Indians alive. The pair's unbeaten 56-run stand off 21 balls secured a third win in nine matches, keeping Mumbai Indians alive in the season

name: Chennai Super Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: Super Kings won by 6 wickets (with 12 balls remaining)
highlights: Jadeja and Harbhajan sink the RCB arsenal. The CSK spinners took out RCB's big guns within the first eight overs and from thereon turned a blockbuster contest into damp squib

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Delhi Daredevils
result: Sunrisers won by 7 wickets (with 1 ball remaining)
highlights: Sunrisers pull off their season's best chase to go No. 1. Rashid Khan led an inspired bowling performance to restrict Daredevils to 163 after a bright start, and Sunrisers' batsmen just about managed to overhaul that total

name: Mumbai Indians v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Hardik delivers twice at the death to keep Mumbai alive. The allrounder made an unbeaten 35 off 20 and followed up with figures of 2 for 19 in four overs to help Mumbai Indians shade KKR in a constantly fluctuating contest

name: Punjab Kings v Rajasthan Royals
result: Kings XI won by 6 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
highlights: Rahul aces chase to end Kings XI's losing run. Rajasthan Royals' hopes of a playoffs spot took a beating after their sixth defeat in nine games

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Williamson, Rashid all but seal RCB's fate. Sunrisers Hyderabad produced another masterclass at defending a small total after their captain's 56 lifted them to 146

name: Rajasthan Royals v Punjab Kings
highlights: KL Rahul unbeaten, but Royals beat rest of Kings XI. Jos Buttler's 82 had set Rajasthan Royals up for a bigger total than 158, but a dry pitch became progressively slower and kept Kings XI Punjab from coming anywhere close

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Ishan Kishan powers Mumbai Indians into IPL's top four for the first time. Kolkata Knight Riders suffered a heavy defeat that led to them dropping to fifth in the league, after considerable time in the top four

name: Delhi Daredevils v Sunrisers Hyderabad
result: Sunrisers won by 9 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Pant's epic ton in vain as Sunrisers reach playoffs. Kane Williamson and Shikhar Dhawan aced the chase of 188 with no fuss to knock Delhi Daredevils out

name: Rajasthan Royals v Chennai Super Kings
result: Royals won by 4 wickets (with 1 ball remaining)
highlights: Buttler keeps Royals relevant in race to playoffs. In a game that Rajasthan Royals had to win to stay in playoff contention, their opener Jos Buttler struck his fourth fifty in a row to seal a four-wicket final-over win against CSK

name: Punjab Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: KKR flatten Kings XI with season-topping 245. Sunil Narine's 36-ball 75 and Dinesh Karthik's 23-ball 50 outdid KL Rahul's 29-ball 66 in a match that produced an aggregate of 459 runs

name: Delhi Daredevils v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 5 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Kohli and de Villiers combine to knock Daredevils out of contention. Royal Challengers' stalwarts made a combined 142 of the 182 they required to collect their fourth win so far

name: Chennai Super Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad
result: Super Kings won by 8 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Rayudu hundred puts CSK on brink of playoffs. Chennai Super Kings all but joined Sunrisers Hyderabad in the playoffs with a dominant win over the leaders of the league

name: Mumbai Indians v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Buttler makes easy work of Mumbai to lift Royals to fifth place. Buttler made a domineering, unbeaten 94 off 53 balls, his fifth consecutive IPL fifty, to vault Rajasthan Royals to fifth on the table

name: Punjab Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 10 wickets (with 71 balls remaining)
highlights: Umesh Yadav leads RCB's rout of Kings XI. A mix of short balls and run-outs helped skittle Kings XI for 88. Royal Challengers knocked those runs off with almost 12 overs to spare

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Rajasthan Royals
result: KKR won by 6 wickets (with 12 balls remaining)
highlights: Kuldeep, Russell push KKR closer to playoffs. The two were instrumental in restricting Rajasthan Royals to 142 after Jos Buttler and Rahul Tripathi had powered them to 59 for 0 in four overs

name: Mumbai Indians v Punjab Kings
highlights: Bumrah and Pollard keep Mumbai alive. KL Rahul struck 94 off 60 and Andrew Tye claimed 4 for 16 but Kings XI finished on the losing side

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: Williamson special in vain as de Villiers, Moeen keep RCB alive. Kane Williamson made a rousing 81 off 42 balls but it wasn't enough for Sunrisers Hyderabad to chase down 219

name: Delhi Daredevils v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Harshal, Mishra help Daredevils trip up CSK. Harshal's unbeaten 36, including a 26-run final over off Dwayne Bravo, proved to be the game-changer, with CSK not yet assured of a top-two spot

name: Rajasthan Royals v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Bengaluru boys knock out RCB, Royals stay alive. Shreyas Gopal's 4 for 16 and K Gowtham's all-round display sent RCB tumbling out of the tournament with a 30-run defeat in Jaipur

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 5 wickets (with 2 balls remaining)
highlights: Narine, Lynn and Uthappa book KKR's playoffs spot. Kolkata Knight Riders put in yet another spirited performance to win their final league game by five wickets and consigning Sunrisers Hyderabad to their third straight loss

name: Delhi Daredevils v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Daredevils knock out Mumbai, Royals dare to dream. Legspinners Amit Mishra and Sandeep Lamichhane took three wickets each after Rishabh Pant scored a superb half-century

name: Chennai Super Kings v Punjab Kings
result: Super Kings won by 5 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
highlights: Ngidi, Raina knock Kings XI out; Royals secure playoffs spot. Lungi Ngidi bowled a fiery spell of 4 for 10 to keep Kings XI to 153 before a strong and changed CSK line-up changed it down

name: Rising Pune Supergiant v Mumbai Indians
result: Supergiant won by 7 wickets (with 1 ball remaining)
highlights: Rahane, Smith clinch thriller for Pune. An ice-cool unbeaten 84 from Steven Smith steered Rising Pune Supergiant to a seven-wicket win against Mumbai Indians at the MCA Stadium

name: Gujarat Lions v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 10 wickets (with 31 balls remaining)
highlights: Gambhir, Lynn blaze away in record chase. Kolkata Knight Riders gunned down a target of 184 without losing a single wicket - a world record in T20 cricket

name: Punjab Kings v Rising Pune Supergiant
result: Kings XI won by 6 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Bowlers' strangle, Maxwell flash gives Kings XI success. The Kings XI Punjab bowlers restricted Rising Pune Supergiants to a total of 163 which Glenn Maxwell, on captaincy debut, helped overhaul with an over to spare.

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Royal Challengers defend 157 despite Pant's belligerence. Royal Challengers Bangalore defended 157 at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium against Delhi Daredevils to register their first win of the tournament

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Gujarat Lions
result: Sunrisers won by 9 wickets (with 27 balls remaining)
highlights: Warner, Rashid give Lions a thrashing. Rashid Khan and David Warner combined to ease Sunrisers Hyderabad to their second win of the season, and send Gujarat Lions crashing to another huge defeat

name: Mumbai Indians v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: Mum Indians won by 4 wickets (with 1 ball remaining)
highlights: Rana, Pandya brothers stage stunning heist. On a high-scoring, field-first ground, fighting considerable amount of dew, Kolkata Knight Riders nearly won with an under-par 178 but failed to defend 59 in the last 23 balls

name: Punjab Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: Kings XI won by 8 wickets (with 33 balls remaining)
highlights: Kings XI overcome de Villiers' one-man show. AB de Villiers made a jaw-dropping 89 off 46 balls, but the rest of Royal Challengers Bangalore was so woeful that Kings XI Punjab won with 33 balls to spare

name: Rising Pune Supergiant v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Samson's maiden ton razes Rising Pune. A maiden T20 hundred from Sanju Samson and a blistering unbeaten 38, off just nine balls, from Chris Morris, led Delhi Daredevils to their first win of the season, a 97-run mauling of Rising Pune Supergiant

name: Mumbai Indians v Sunrisers Hyderabad
result: Mum Indians won by 4 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
highlights: Mumbai sail home on dewy evening. Harbhajan Singh and Jasprit Bumrah bowled accurate and misery spells on a typically high-scoring ground to condemn Sunrisers Hyderabad to their first defeat in six matches

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Punjab Kings
result: KKR won by 8 wickets (with 21 balls remaining)
highlights: Gambhir, Umesh script Kings XI thrashing. Led by Umesh Yadav's 4 for 33, Kolkata Knight Riders restricted Kings XI Punjab to 170, a total they chased down with eight wickets in hand

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 4 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Pollard fifty overcomes Badree hat-trick. Kieron Pollard's 47-ball 70 hauled Mumbai Indians to a six-wicket win against Royal Challengers Bangalore, for whom a Samuel Badree hat-trick wasn't enough to defend 142

name: Gujarat Lions v Rising Pune Supergiant
result: Guj Lions won by 7 wickets (with 12 balls remaining)
highlights: Debutant Tye's five-for fashions Lions' first win. Andrew Tye picked up 5 for 17 - the best figures for an IPL debutant - to lead Gujarat Lions to their first victory in IPL 2017

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Sunrisers Hyderabad
highlights: KKR top table with Uthappa and spinners. In an error-strewn match, Bhuvneshwar Kumar and Kuldeep Yadav bowled equally immaculate spells, but it was Kolkata Knight Riders who came away with their third win of the season and jumped to the top of the points table

name: Delhi Daredevils v Punjab Kings
highlights: Billings, Anderson dismantle Kings XI. Crucial innings from Corey Anderson - 39* off 22 balls - and Sam Billings - 55 off 40 - helped Delhi Daredevils post their second win in three matches

name: Mumbai Indians v Gujarat Lions
result: Mum Indians won by 6 wickets (with 3 balls remaining)
highlights: Rana, Rohit, Pollard seal another Wankhede chase. The chase-friendly image of Wankhede survived a test as Mumbai Indians chased down 177 on a slow pitch with three balls to spare

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Rising Pune Supergiant
highlights: Pune quicks defend 161 against RCB. Rising Pune Supergiant's middle order froze on sluggish Chinnaswamy track, losing five wickets for three runs, but their bowlers bailed them out of trouble in emphatic fashion

name: Delhi Daredevils v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 4 wickets (with 1 ball remaining)
highlights: Pandey, Yusuf give KKR top position after tense chase. Manish Pandey and Yusuf Pathan put on a match-turning stand of 110 in 12 overs to lead KKR's chase as they went on top of the table

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Punjab Kings
highlights: Bhuvneshwar five-for trumps Vohra's 95. A five-wicket haul from Bhuvneshwar Kumar won Sunrisers Hyderabad a tight game against  Kings XI Punjab despite a 50-ball 95 from Manan Vohra

name: Gujarat Lions v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Gayle blitz, Chahal guile reinvigorate RCB. Royal Challengers Bangalore revived a stalled campaign with a morale-boosting 21-run win, their second in six matches

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Williamson and Dhawan overwhelm Daredevils. Kane Williamson, playing his first match of the season, made an imperious 89 off 51 balls and propelled Sunrisers Hyderabad to their fourth win in four home matches

name: Punjab Kings v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 8 wickets (with 27 balls remaining)
highlights: Mumbai top order destroys Kings XI in highest successful chase. Quickfire fifties from Jos Buttler and Nitish Rana trumped Hashim Amla's century as Mumbai Indians completed their highest successful chase in the IPL

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Gujarat Lions
result: Guj Lions won by 4 wickets (with 10 balls remaining)
highlights: Raina assault too hot for Knight Riders. Suresh Raina's 46-ball 84 helped Gujarat Lions ace a potentially tough chase of 188 with 10 balls to spare

name: Delhi Daredevils v Royal Challengers Bangalore

name: Punjab Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium

name: Chennai Super Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders

name: Punjab Kings v Mumbai Indians

name: Chennai Super Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Sunrisers Hyderabad

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Punjab Kings

name: Delhi Daredevils v Sunrisers Hyderabad
venue_name: Shaheed Veer Narayan Singh International Stadium
highlights: Sunrisers hold nerve to move fourth. name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Punjab Kings
highlights: Nervy Sunrisers survive Miller blitz. David Warner continued to carry his team forward in the tournament on the back of his own personal form, his sixth half-century this season laying the foundation of Sunrisers Hyderabad's fifth win in six matches that helped them catch up with Rajasthan Ro

name: Delhi Daredevils v Chennai Super Kings
result: Daredevils won by 6 wickets (with 20 balls remaining)

venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium

name: Chennai Super Kings v Punjab Kings

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Rajasthan Royals

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Delhi Daredevils

name: Rajasthan Royals v Punjab Kings

name: Chennai Super Kings v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: CSK crush Daredevils by 93 runs. Chennai Super Kings crushed Delhi Daredevils by 93 runs in a thoroughly one-sided game in Abu Dhabi

name: Punjab Kings v Sunrisers Hyderabad

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Delhi Daredevils

name: Chennai Super Kings v Mumbai Indians

name: Mumbai Indians v Punjab Kings

name: Delhi Daredevils v Kolkata Knight Riders

name: Mumbai Indians v Chennai Super Kings

name: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Punjab Kings

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Mumbai Indians
result: KKR won by 6 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Chennai Super Kings

name: Punjab Kings v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 7 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Royal Challengers Bangalore

name: Punjab Kings v Rajasthan Royals

name: Punjab Kings v Delhi Daredevils
result: Kings XI won by 7 wickets (with 37 balls remaining)

name: Mumbai Indians v Rajasthan Royals

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Delhi Daredevils

highlights: Last-ball six keeps Chennai alive. With Chennai Super Kings needing five runs to win off the final delivery, Rajat Bhatia bowled a full toss which Dwayne Bravo heaved over the long-on boundary

name: Delhi Daredevils v Punjab Kings
result: Daredevils won by 5 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Mahela guides Delhi into playoffs. Mahela Jayawardene's half-century may have been the slowest for Delhi Daredevils this season but it helped his team become the first side to qualify for the playoffs

name: Mumbai Indians v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Narine mystery too much for Mumbai. Kolkata Knight Riders are as good as through to the playoffs after Sunil Narine inspired them to a win over Mumbai Indians

name: Punjab Kings v Chennai Super Kings
result: Kings XI won by 6 wickets (with 21 balls remaining)
highlights: Gilchrist, seamers push Chennai to the brink. Kings XI Punjab kept themselves in contention for a place in the playoffs with a comfortable victory set up by their seamers in Dharamsala

name: Delhi Daredevils v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Gayle ton delivers crucial win for Bangalore. Chris Gayle and Virat Kohli took 204 runs off a Morne Morkel-less attack to lead Royal Challengers to the highest total of 2012, one that was ultimately a match-winning one

name: Deccan Chargers v Rajasthan Royals
result: Chargers won by 5 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
highlights: Rajasthan crash out as batting flops. Rajasthan Royals were knocked out of the playoff race by a stifling spell of legspin bowling from Amit Mishra

name: Punjab Kings v Delhi Daredevils
result: Daredevils won by 6 wickets (with 10 balls remaining)
highlights: Delhi knock out Punjab and take top spot. Delhi Daredevils confirmed their standing as the team to beat with a power-packed performance to knock out Kings XI Punjab

name: Pune Warriors v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Shakib lifts Kolkata to No. 2 spot. Kolkata Knight Riders set up a first qualifier match against table-toppers Delhi Daredevils as they took the No. 2 spot with a comfortable win over Pune Warriors

name: Deccan Chargers v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Steyn, Duminy help Deccan knock out RCB. Royal Challengers Bangalore imploded in their most crucial match of the season, choking in a low-scoring chase and bowing out of race for the playoffs

name: Rajasthan Royals v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 10 wickets (with 12 balls remaining)
highlights: Smith and Tendulkar crush Rajasthan. Dwayne Smith and Sachin Tendulkar, with the help of a large dose of luck, put on the highest stand for the first wicket to crush Rajasthan Royals

name: Chennai Super Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Chennai sneak last-ball victory. Chennai grabbed a two-run last-ball victory over Kolkata in the opening game of the season

name: Deccan Chargers v Rajasthan Royals
result: Royals won by 8 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Botha, Trivedi star as Rajasthan open with a win. Sidharth Trivedi choked Deccan's run flow with a canny spell of slow bouncers, before Johan Botha, elevated to the No. 3 spot, guided them past the target of 138 in the 19th over

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 6 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
highlights: Cool de Villiers crashes Kochi party. Four blistering sixes from AB de Villiers won the night for Bangalore Royal Challengers

name: Delhi Daredevils v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 8 wickets (with 19 balls remaining)
highlights: Malinga's five sets up comfortable Mumbai win. Lasith Malinga's five-wicket haul helped shoot out Delhi for 95, their second-lowest total, and ruin the contest before the sun had set at the Feroz Shah Kotla

name: Pune Warriors v Punjab Kings
result: Warriors won by 7 wickets (with 41 balls remaining)
highlights: Pune Warriors flatten listless Punjab. Pune Warriors outclassed Kings XI Punjab by seven wickets at the DY Patil Stadium

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Kallis shines in Kolkata's home victory. On a turning track where the ball kept low, Kolkata's batsmen all chipped in to put up the highest total of the tournament so far, which proved sufficient against Deccan Chargers

name: Rajasthan Royals v Delhi Daredevils
result: Royals won by 6 wickets (with 9 balls remaining)
highlights: Rajasthan Royals surge to second win. Rajasthan Royals executed a well-calibrated chase against an off-colour Delhi Daredevils attack to register their second win in two games and move atop the IPL leaderboard

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 9 wickets (with 9 balls remaining)
highlights: All-round Mumbai coast past Bangalore. Sachin Tendulkar, the controller, and Ambati Rayudu, the enforcer, made short work of the below-par target to give Mumbai their second successive win of the tournament

name: Punjab Kings v Chennai Super Kings
result: Kings XI won by 6 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Valthaty ton pulls off superb chase. India's northernmost franchise found a new hero with roots deep down south, as Paul Valthaty stunned Chennai Super Kings in an outstanding counterattack that clinched a maiden win for Kings XI Punjab this season

name: Pune Warriors v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
result: Warriors won by 4 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Pune win clash of new teams. A fluctuating game between the two new teams in the tournament ended with Pune Warriors at the top of the table and Kochi Tuskers Kerala near the other end

name: Deccan Chargers v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Deccan charge to maiden home victory. Accurate spells of fast bowling from the entire cast of seamers helped Deccan Chargers inflict a convincing 33-run victory over Royal Challengers Bangalore, who have now suffered two losses in a row

name: Rajasthan Royals v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 9 wickets (with 9 balls remaining)
highlights: Gambhir, Kallis set up thumping win. It shouldn't have been that easy but Gautam Gambhir and Jacques Kallis starred in a supremely well-paced chase as Kolkata successfully hunted down a potentially tough 160-run target on a sluggish track in Jaipur.

name: Mumbai Indians v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
result: Kochi won by 8 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Kochi upstage Tendulkar's century. On Friday, the crowd at the Wankhede returned dejected despite Tendulkar crafting his maiden Twenty20 century as Kochi Kerala Tuskers busted their party with one of the most memorable chases in IPL history

name: Chennai Super Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Hussey sets up comfortable win for Chennai. A sparkling 83 from Michael Hussey lifted Chennai to a strong score, and the lack of Paul Valthaty-esque intent in the Bangalore batting meant it proved to be a winning score

name: Deccan Chargers v Punjab Kings
result: Kings XI won by 8 wickets (with 14 balls remaining)
highlights: Midas Valthaty gives Punjab comprehensive win. Paul Valthaty followed up his century in the previous game by surprising everybody with his split-finger slower balls, taking 4 for 29 and then - with a 47-ball 75 - making mockery of a target he had himself kept down to 165

name: Pune Warriors v Delhi Daredevils
result: Daredevils won by 3 wickets (with 4 balls remaining)
highlights: Delhi outdo Yuvraj's all-round show. Delhi Daredevils' revamped batting order pulled its weight to complete a thrilling chase at the DY Patil Staduim in Mumbai, securing their maiden victory after two losses

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Rajasthan Royals
result: KKR won by 8 wickets (with 37 balls remaining)
highlights: Balaji stars in crushing win. L Balaji produced some magic, Shakib Al Hasan had a double strike and the fielders hustled as  Kolkata Knight Riders routed Rajasthan by eight wickets

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Chennai Super Kings
result: Kochi won by 7 wickets (with 12 balls remaining) (D/L method)
highlights: Spirited Kochi make it two in two. Brendon McCullum made a severe dent into the below-par D/L-adjusted target, and handy contributions from Parthiv Patel and Brad Hodge then gave Kochi Tuskers their second win in a row

name: Mumbai Indians v Pune Warriors
result: Mum Indians won by 7 wickets (with 0 balls remaining)
highlights: Mumbai beat ordinary Pune. Facing some stifling bowling on a bouncy track, Pune Warriors put in an ordinary effort with the bat to concede Mumbai Indians two fairly easy points

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
highlights: Kochi stifle Kolkata in hard-fought win. Kochi Tuskers Kerala won a battle of attrition against Kolkata Knight Riders on a slow Eden Gardens pitch that aided the spinners, in the process moving third position in the points table

name: Punjab Kings v Rajasthan Royals
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Brutal Punjab maul ragged Rajasthan. Shaun Marsh built on the openers' heroics as Kings XI Punjab roared to a score of 195, setting up their third successive win, against a ragged Rajasthan Royals outfit

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 9 wickets (with 11 balls remaining)
highlights: Gayle announces himself with ton. Chris Gayle smashed his way to his first IPL century, the second fastest in this edition of the competition, and was the architect of Bangalore's victory over his former team, Kolkata

name: Mumbai Indians v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Chennai fall to Harbhajan five-for. Rohit Sharma dazzled the senses, Harbhajan Singh sucker-punched with three wickets in an over, and Mumbai Indians hustled on the field to go around a sublime S Badrinath and clinch a well-fought win at the Wankhede Stadium

name: Delhi Daredevils v Punjab Kings
highlights: Delhi back to winning ways on green track. The rampant opening firm of Virender Sehwag and David Warner set up a comprehensive win for Delhi Daredevils despite an equally remarkable innings by Shaun Marsh

name: Deccan Chargers v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Rohit, Malinga lead Mumbai to impressive win. Deccan Chargers had the chance to retain Rohit Sharma and Andrew Symonds, but let both of them go, and paid the price today

name: Rajasthan Royals v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
result: Royals won by 8 wickets (with 35 balls remaining)
highlights: Warne leads Rajasthan to emphatic win. Cosmetic surgery? Moisturiser? Who cares? Shane Warne is still ripping them legbreaks

name: Chennai Super Kings v Pune Warriors
highlights: Rampant Chennai smother Pune in the field. A disciplined performance from Chennai Super Kings in the field saw them get their IPL campaign back on track as they comfortably defended 142 against the Pune Warriors

name: Delhi Daredevils v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 3 wickets (with 3 balls remaining)
highlights: Bangalore win in seesaw chase. The Royal Challengers Bangalore lower order scraped 22 runs from 15 deliveries to steer their side past Delhi Daredevils' 160 - a target that had looked small while Virat Kohli was in the middle

name: Pune Warriors v Chennai Super Kings
result: Super Kings won by 8 wickets (with 3 balls remaining)
highlights: Classy Badrinath stars in easy win. S Badrinath walked into a tricky situation, took charge of the chase without playing a single ugly shot, and finessed Chennai Super Kings to No. 2 in the IPL table with an easy win, though the game ended in the final over

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Ishant five-for wrecks Kochi. The Kochi Tuskers Kerala scorecard read 11 for 6 at the end of four overs as their batsmen were sucker-punched by Ishant Sharma, who harassed them with seam and bounce. And Kochi never recovered from that soul-crushing spell.

name: Delhi Daredevils v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Kolkata fight back to keep Delhi bottom. Kolkata Knight Riders showed their mettle to pull off an 18-run victory on a two-paced Feroz Shah Kotla track

name: Rajasthan Royals v Mumbai Indians
result: Royals won by 7 wickets (with 11 balls remaining)
highlights: Botha stars as Rajasthan hammer Mumbai. Mumbai Indians' first batting collapse of the tournament gave Rajasthan Royals a small target of 95, which they chase on a dry and cracked pitch in Jaipur

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Pune Warriors
highlights: Kohli, Gayle star as Bangalore sink Pune. Pune Warriors went up against Murphy's Law at the Chinnaswamy Stadium and came a distant second-best, as they hurtled to their fifth successive defeat

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Delhi rout Kochi after Sehwag masterclass. Virender Sehwag showcased his class on a tricky surface on which numerous deliveries hardly got up above ankle height, exploding in the end to lift Delhi Daredevils to 157, a score that proved beyond Kochi Tuskers Kerala

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Punjab Kings
result: KKR won by 8 wickets (with 16 balls remaining)
highlights: Kolkata out-spin Punjab on turner. On a square turner, Kolkata Knight Riders out-spun Kings XI Punjab to move to become joint leaders on the point table

name: Rajasthan Royals v Pune Warriors
result: Royals won by 6 wickets (with 3 balls remaining)
highlights: Taylor leads Rajasthan to top spot. Rahul Sharma threatened to win it but Murali Kartik lost the plot and Rajasthan's Ross Taylor seized the moment, with valuable support from Ajinkya Rahane, to clinch a thrilling win

name: Chennai Super Kings v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Smart Chennai withstand Sohal blinder. Sunny Sohal was like a millionaire spending the last night of his life in Las Vegas, but as it often happens in heist films, the casino owners withstood the brilliant early hand

name: Mumbai Indians v Punjab Kings
highlights: Ruthless Mumbai surge to sixth win. Sachin Tendulkar and Ambati Rayudu took Mumbai to 159, a gettable score on this pitch, but not against an attack as ruthless as their's

name: Delhi Daredevils v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
result: Kochi won by 7 wickets (with 30 balls remaining)
highlights: All-round Kochi pummel Delhi. Mahela Jayawardene's men outclassed Delhi, snapping a three-game losing streak by cruising to victory with five overs to go

name: Deccan Chargers v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Yusuf and Co. make sloppy Deccan Chargers pay. Deccan Chargers dropped too many catches in the first half of the game to allow Kolkata Knight Riders to motor along to 169, and then dropped intensity alarmingly in the chase to succumb to their sixth defeat in nine games

name: Chennai Super Kings v Rajasthan Royals
result: Super Kings won by 8 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
highlights: All-round Chennai cruise to fourth straight win. An inspired recovery from Chennai's faltering bowlers and a controlled approach to the chase from Suresh Raina and Michael Hussey lay at the heart of a comfortable win

name: Pune Warriors v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Mumbai win edges Pune closer to exit. Mumbai proved they are the best team in the tournament and reclaimed their by now customary at the summit of the table by battering Pune at the DY Patil Stadium

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Gomez and Hodge star in hard-fought win. A disciplined performance in the field and an explosive 35 off 19 balls from Brad Hodge helped Kochi Tuskers overcome Kolkata Knight Riders in the last match at the Nehru stadium

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Punjab Kings
highlights: Punjab succumb to merciless Gayle. Once every two years, Bangalore hosts Aero India, the country's biggest air show held on the outskirts of the city. On Friday night, Chris Gayle took it upon himself to deliver a similar spectacle to the home crowd

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Bowlers set up victory for Kolkata. Kolkata Knight Riders' bowlers made best use of a sluggish pitch after a rain-delayed start, keeping Chennai Super Kings to 114, and their batsmen did enough to be ahead of the par score when rain returned to cut the match short

name: Mumbai Indians v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Rayudu, bowlers lead Mumbai to dominant win. Mumbai Indians played like the dominant side they have been this IPL, and Delhi Daredevils like the middling one they have been

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
result: RCB won by 9 wickets (with 41 balls remaining)
highlights: Brilliant Bangalore demolish Kochi. The hapless Kochi Tuskers Kerala ran into each facet of Bangalore's brilliance, and were dismantled clinically in a nine-wicket hiding, that came with 6.5 overs to spare

name: Punjab Kings v Pune Warriors
result: Warriors won by 5 wickets (with 17 balls remaining)
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Pune finally snap losing streak. Pune Warriors finally ended their horror run of seven defeats by limiting fellow stragglers Kings XI Punjab to 119 in Mohali, a target which didn't tax their batting too much

name: Rajasthan Royals v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Chennai breach fortress Jaipur. Chennai Super Kings' powerful batting line-up was back to top form to spoil Shane Warne's first game since announcing his retirement

name: Deccan Chargers v Pune Warriors
result: Warriors won by 6 wickets (with 10 balls remaining)
highlights: Disciplined Pune outplay uninspired Deccan. Deccan Chargers were handcuffed by Yuvraj Singh's round-arm left-arm spin, submitting to a middling total after a flashy start

name: Punjab Kings v Mumbai Indians
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Sloppy Mumbai succumb in big upset. After a glut of one-sided snooze-fests, the IPL produced the kind of upset the Twenty20 format is made for, with the tenth-placed Kings XI Punjab producing a strong performance to trounce the table-toppers, Mumbai Indians

name: Rajasthan Royals v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 9 wickets (with 18 balls remaining)
highlights: Powerful Bangalore outclass Rajasthan. For the second successive match, Rajasthan Royals played on a true surface that did not suit them, and yet again, they were outclassed by a side that was clearly superior in all departments

name: Chennai Super Kings v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Chennai closer to play-offs with comprehensive win. Chennai Super Kings all but ensured qualification for the playoffs, and took an important step towards ending in the crucial top two, with a win that withstood the odd scare from Delhi Daredevils

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Punjab Kings
result: Kings XI won by 6 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Karthik blitz keeps Punjab in race. Kings XI Punjab beat the Kochi Tuskers Kerala by six wickets in a boundary-rich encounter at the IPL's newest venue, Indore

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: RCB won by 4 wickets (with 3 balls remaining) (D/L method)
highlights: Gayle cameo takes Bangalore through to play-offs. Brett Lee sledged, Gautam Gambhir sighed in agony, and the crowd lapped it up in delight as Chris Gayle's brutal cameo obliterated the below-par target set by Kolkata Knight Riders in a rain-hit game in Bangalore

name: Mumbai Indians v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Deccan prevail in low-scoring upset. For 19 overs, Deccan Chargers, out of the competition already, seemed to be going through their motions

name: Punjab Kings v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Average Delhi keep Punjab's campaign alive. Punjab's bowlers, led by a resurgent Piyush Chawla, capitalised on Delhi's woes to run to their third win on the trot, keeping their late-blooming campaign alive

name: Kochi Tuskers Kerala v Rajasthan Royals
result: Kochi won by 8 wickets (with 76 balls remaining)
highlights: Kochi stay mathematically alive with a thumping win. The short boundaries in Indore proved to be bad masters for Rajasthan Royals

name: Pune Warriors v Deccan Chargers
result: Chargers won by 6 wickets (with 4 balls remaining)
highlights: Deccan end Pune's slim hopes. A bowling attack having four Test bowlers bowled to its world-class potential for once and Deccan Chargers' batting did not stumble chasing a middling total to end Pune Warriors slim hopes of making the play-offs

name: Punjab Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Sizzling Gilchrist conquers Bangalore. Adam Gilchrist rolled back the years to produce a delightfully aggressive century and Shaun Marsh unfurled a gem of his own to charge Kings XI Punjab to a thumping victory

name: Chennai Super Kings v Kochi Tuskers Kerala
highlights: Determined Chennai surge to top spot. The MA Chidambaram Stadium continued to be a fortress that couldn't be breached, as Chennai sealed a seventh straight win at home to end Kochi Tuskers Kerala's maiden IPL campaign on a disappointing note

name: Pune Warriors v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: KKR won by 7 wickets (with 20 balls remaining)
highlights: Spinners, Gambhir help Kolkata breeze past Pune. Shakib Al Hasan, Iqbal Abdulla  and Yusuf Pathan tied Pune down, exploiting the generous spin available on the DY Patil Stadium surface, and Gautam Gambhir ensured that his side motored to victory in the 17th over

name: Mumbai Indians v Rajasthan Royals
result: Royals won by 10 wickets (with 41 balls remaining)
highlights: Mumbai humbled by the other Shane. The prospect of a final face-off between Sachin Tendulkar and Shane Warne had dominated the build-up to this clash, but on the field it was overshadowed by an imposing performance from Shane Watson

name: Punjab Kings v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Dhawan puts Punjab out of contention. The happy ever-after fairytale ending to the league phase campaign that Kings XI Punjab were expecting slipped through their fingers, literally, in Dharamsala

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Chennai Super Kings
result: RCB won by 8 wickets (with 12 balls remaining)
highlights: Bangalore finish on top of table. Chris Gayle indulged himself after his bowlers restricted Chennai Super Kings to a below-par 128 to ensure Royal Challengers Bangalore will finish top of the points table

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Mumbai Indians
result: Mum Indians won by 5 wickets (with 0 balls remaining)
highlights: Mumbai edge past Kolkata in last-ball finish. Kolkata Knight Riders had their Champions League debut all but booked when they began the last over with 21 to defend

name: Deccan Chargers v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: Deccan choke after Mathews, Shah comeback. Kolkata Knight Riders showed more character than perhaps the first two seasons put together to survive early blows by oldies Chaminda Vaas and Adam Gilchrist at the start of each innings

name: Mumbai Indians v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Mumbai survive special Yusuf ton. The second-fastest Twenty20 hundred, a 37-ball assault from Yusuf Pathan, as delicate as it was brutal, wasn't enough on a day that precious little was contributed by the other Rajasthan Royals players

name: Punjab Kings v Delhi Daredevils
result: Daredevils won by 5 wickets (with 1 ball remaining)
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Gautam Gambhir stars in tense Delhi win. Gautam Gambhir followed up inspired moves in the field with an old-fashioned innings full of sensible strokeplay and saved a glittering batting line-up the blushes in a straightforward chase

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: KKR won by 7 wickets (with 4 balls remaining)
highlights: Kolkata hand Bangalore a pasting. Angelo Mathews starred with the ball before the fireworks from Kolkata Knight Riders openers eased them to two wins in two games

name: Chennai Super Kings v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Deccan big guns overwhelm Chennai. Each apparently content in their post-international careers, Adam Gilchrist, Andrew Symonds and Chaminda Vaas still have the ability and sheer presence to turn a team's mood upside down in one evening

name: Rajasthan Royals v Delhi Daredevils
result: Daredevils won by 6 wickets (with 17 balls remaining)
highlights: Sehwag powers Delhi to convincing victory. A disciplined performance by the Delhi Daredevils bowlers and a blistering innings from Virender Sehwag inflicted a dispiriting defeat on Rajasthan Royals, their second in as many games, in Ahmedabad

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Punjab Kings
result: RCB won by 8 wickets (with 7 balls remaining)
highlights: Blazing Kallis gets Bangalore off the mark. At the halfway mark it seemed as if Punjab had scored enough to record their first victory of the tournament, but Bangalore went after the target with such vengeance that Punjab were punished for trespassing on private property

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Dhoni masterminds facile win for Chennai. MS Dhoni and S Badrinath added a quick, unbroken 109-run stand to push Chennai to a competitive total before their bowlers turned in an inspired performance to bowl them to a surprisingly facile win at the Eden Gardens

name: Delhi Daredevils v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Delhi fizzle out after Tendulkar, Tiwary onslaught. Intimidating sixties by Sachin Tendulkar and Saurabh Tiwary, supported by a cameo from Ambati Rayudu, paved the way for an easy win for Mumbai Indians against Delhi Daredevils

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Rajasthan Royals
result: RCB won by 10 wickets (with 56 balls remaining)
highlights: Dominant  Bangalore crush Rajasthan. A superlative bowling performance by Royal Challengers Bangalore, including a hat-trick by Praveen Kumar, decimated Rajasthan Royals for a paltry 92 and set up a huge win

name: Delhi Daredevils v Chennai Super Kings
result: Super Kings won by 5 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
highlights: Hayden turns big chase into cakewalk. Matthew Hayden and the Mongoose combined in a deadly manner as Hayden smacked 93 off 43 to almost singlehandedly chase down Delhi Daredevils' 185

name: Deccan Chargers v Punjab Kings
highlights: Symonds helps Deccan to first home win. Deccan Chargers survived a late Irfan Pathan assault to seal their first win against Kings XI Punjab in IPL history

name: Rajasthan Royals v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: All-round Rajasthan seal maiden win. Finally, Rajasthan clicked as a unit. And finally, they won a game.  It was a slow wicket, and Rajasthan, whose batsmen were harassed on bouncier pitches in this tournament so far, immediately looked more at home

name: Mumbai Indians v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 7 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
highlights: Vinay, Steyn set up comprehensive win. R Vinay Kumar removed Sachin Tendulkar, Dwayne Bravo and Ambati Rayudu in one over to turn a cat-and-mouse game until then unmistakably Royal Challengers' way, also taking them to the top of the table

name: Mumbai Indians v Kolkata Knight Riders
result: Mum Indians won by 7 wickets (with 9 balls remaining)
highlights: Tendulkar and bowlers help Mumbai cruise. A graceful Sachin Tendulkar fifty was the highlight of Mumbai Indians' convincing seven-wicket win, which was set up by the bowlers who stuck to a strategy to restrict Kolkata Knight Riders to an underwhelming score at the Brabourne Stadium

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Robin Uthappa's blitz floors Chennai. Robin Uthappa's blitz helped his team recover from a shaky start, after which Bangalore's bowlers throttled Chennai to move to the top of the points table

name: Punjab Kings v Rajasthan Royals
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Rajasthan seal valuable victory. Rajasthan Royals backed up a strong batting performance from Adam Voges and Faiz Fazal with a disciplined bowling effort that choked Kings XI Punjab after their top order had delivered a promising start

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Delhi Daredevils
highlights: Kedar Jadhav helps Delhi end losing streak. David Warner exploded at the top and Kedar Jadhav provided a fiery finish to charge Delhi to a strong 183 which they defended with relative ease

name: Mumbai Indians v Chennai Super Kings
result: Mum Indians won by 5 wickets (with 6 balls remaining)
highlights: Tendulkar powers Mumbai to the top. Sachin Tendulkar was the rudder, Shikhar Dhawan provided propulsion, and they combined for a 92-run opening partnership which charted Mumbai Indians' course for success at the Brabourne Stadium

name: Rajasthan Royals v Deccan Chargers
result: Royals won by 8 wickets (with 26 balls remaining)
highlights: Bowlers set up Rajasthan's hat-trick of wins. Shane Warne did not set the IPL alight in his first five matches this season, but he was terrific tonight in Ahmedabad, setting up Rajasthan's third win in a row

name: Punjab Kings v Kolkata Knight Riders
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Kolkata secure much-needed victory. Manoj Tiwary exploded after a slow start and Sourav Ganguly hit a composed half-century to boost Kolkata to 183 which proved beyond the reach of the listless Punjab

name: Rajasthan Royals v Chennai Super Kings
highlights: Rajasthan clinch fourth straight win. Naman Ojha's bat, Yusuf Pathan's right arm and some steady nerves from the fast bowlers proved enough to flummox Chennai Super Kings and lead Rajasthan Royals to their fourth win in a row

name: Deccan Chargers v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Harbhajan sizzles in Mumbai win. Harbhajan Singh needed only 18 balls when he batted and just one delivery when he bowled to win the game for Mumbai Indians

name: Delhi Daredevils v Kolkata Knight Riders
highlights: David Warner hundred hands Delhi huge win. Wickets fell in each of the first three overs, but David Warner batted on some other island, scoring a superb century and setting up a huge win for Delhi

name: Mumbai Indians v Punjab Kings
result: Mum Indians won by 4 wickets (with 3 balls remaining)
highlights: Lasith Malinga, Saurabh Tiwary star in thrilling Mumbai win. A dry slow wicket and the early fall of Sachin Tendulkar, on whom Mumbai tend to depend far too much, combined to produce a thrilling game that concluded in the last over

name: Chennai Super Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Vijay blasts Chennai to vital victory. The fear of an early elimination from the tournament drove Chennai Super Kings to deliver their best all-round performance, that too against the table leaders

name: Delhi Daredevils v Rajasthan Royals
highlights: Karthik helps Delhi crush Rajasthan. Dinesh Karthik hit a delightful half-century on a slow difficult pitch to charge Delhi Daredevils to a facile win against Rajasthan Royals at the Feroz Shah Kotl

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Deccan Chargers
highlights: Sparkling Ganguly stars in vital Kolkata victory. Inspired by their captain and urged on by the cauldron that is the Eden Gardens, Kolkata Knight Riders roared back into the competition with a clinical win over Deccan Chargers

name: Punjab Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
result: RCB won by 6 wickets (with 5 balls remaining)
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium

name: Delhi Daredevils v Punjab Kings
result: Kings XI won by 6 runs (D/L method)
highlights: Punjab edge a rain-reduced game. Not even 20 overs were bowled, but there was no shortage of excitement and drama as the Kings XI Punjab inched closer to a semi-final spot

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Chennai Super Kings
result: Super Kings won by 3 runs (D/L method)
highlights: Chennai clinch rain-reduced game. Chennai Super Kings won a rain-reduced match at the Eden Gardens to notch up their seventh win of the IPL

name: Deccan Chargers v Mumbai Indians
highlights: Bravo seals Mumbai's sixth straight win. Mumbai's last meeting with Deccan ended in a fourth straight defeat but the return game provided plenty of cheer, producing their sixth successive win

name: Royal Challengers Bangalore v Delhi Daredevils
result: Daredevils won by 5 wickets (with 10 balls remaining)
highlights: Delhi secure much-needed win. Bangalore Royal Challengers are out of contention for a spot in the semi-finals following a five-wicket defeat at the hands of the Delhi Daredevils

name: Kolkata Knight Riders v Rajasthan Royals
result: Royals won by 6 wickets (with 21 balls remaining)
highlights: Yusuf powers Rajasthan into semi-finals. A disciplined performance with the ball, followed by a counterattacking blitz from Yusuf Pathan, sealed a six-wicket win at Eden Gardens for the Rajasthan Royals

name: Chennai Super Kings v Royal Challengers Bangalore
highlights: Kumble inspires Bangalore to stunning win. A few hours after the Mumbai Indians collapsed from a winning position, thereby denting their semi-final chances, the Chennai Super Kings outdid them as panic struck at the MA Chidambaram Stadium

name: Punjab Kings v Deccan Chargers
result: Kings XI won by 6 wickets (with 3 balls remaining)
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Marsh and Sangakkara seal close win. Despite having little to play for in this dead rubber, Kings XI Punjab put on an imposing performance against the Deccan Chargers and gave the other teams plenty to think about ahead of the semi-finals

name: Rajasthan Royals v Mumbai Indians
result: Royals won by 5 wickets (with 0 balls remaining)
highlights: Rajasthan secure top spot with last-ball win. The Mumbai Indians lost their third successive nail-biter to leave their semi-final hopes hanging by a thread

name: Punjab Kings v Rajasthan Royals
venue_name: Punjab Cricket Association IS Bindra Stadium
highlights: Marsh century conquers Rajasthan. Kings XI Punjab's top order powered their team to a 41-run win in  a dead-rubber top-of-the-table clash in Mohali
